metadata.name: Eruption
metadata.description:
Digital sunset explosion created from an original sunset photograph by Joanne Enders.

Whose energy is that? I think I know. Its owner is quite angry though.
She was cross like a dark ocean. I watch her pace. I cry hello.
She gives her energy a shake, And screams I've made a bad mistake. The only other sound's the break, Of distant waves and birds awake.
The energy is eruption, wide and deep, But she has promises to keep, Tormented with nightmares she never sleeps. Revenge is a promise to keep.
She rises from her cursed bed, With thoughts of violence in her head, A flash of rage and she sees red. Without a pause I turned and fled.
